    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Oligopeptide-112 SP Amide is a single chain human peptide produced synthetically to be identical to a portion of the protein, Insulin-Like Growth Factor 1, and contains 15 amino acids consisting of glycine, leucine, phenylalanine and tyrosine in which the C-terminus is an amide. The parent protein contains a maximum of 195 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
